            <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
            <html>
            <head>
                <meta http-equiv="Content-type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8" />
            </head>
            <body><h1>Database ticom_COMP2910</h1><h2>Table structure for table secondscene</h2><table class="width100" cellspacing="1"><tr class="print-category"><th class="print">Column</th><td class="print"><strong>Type</strong></td><td class="print"><strong>Null</strong></td><td class="print"><strong>Default</strong></td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print"><em><strong>ID</strong></em></td><td class="print">int(11)</td><td class="print">No</td><td class="print"></td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">dialogue</td><td class="print">text</td><td class="print">Yes</td><td class="print">NULL</td></tr></table><h2>Dumping data for table secondscene</h2><table class="width100" cellspacing="1"><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">1</td><td class="print">We did it! The leaking stopped!</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">2</td><td class="print">We should check the toilets for leaks too...</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">3</td><td class="print">but the leaks must be the reason why we're low on water.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">4</td><td class="print">WRONG.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">5</td><td class="print">The leaking pipes have nothing to do with the shortage of water.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">6</td><td class="print">Who are you?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">7</td><td class="print">The name's Richard.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">8</td><td class="print">For fifteen years I have maintained this hotel.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">9</td><td class="print">You must be the new manager.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">10</td><td class="print">If the leaking pipes didn't cause the water shortage, then what caused it?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">11</td><td class="print">Weather and people.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">12</td><td class="print">???...</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">13</td><td class="print">Thanks to climate change, we get less rainfall and the snow melts earlier during spring.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">14</td><td class="print">Less rainfall and snow melting earlier during spring means we have a lower supply of water in our local reservoir during dry seasons.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">15</td><td class="print">And people?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">16</td><td class="print">How do people contribute to a water shortage?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">17</td><td class="print">Every year, thousands of people move into our town...</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">18</td><td class="print">but since the amount of rainfall we get doesn't change, there just isn't enough water for everyone to use.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">19</td><td class="print">If that's the case, how are we going to find more water...</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">20</td><td class="print">Hm......</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">21</td><td class="print">If we can't get more water, then we have to conserve water.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">22</td><td class="print">While I was collecting water from the leaks, I thought of an idea. Let's go to the hotel's kitchen.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">23</td><td class="print">Wait, I want to check out the garden.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">24</td><td class="print">A lot of water is used for the garden but I want to see if I can find any ways to save some water there.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">25</td><td class="print">Okay, we'll meet back at the lobby later.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">26</td><td class="print">As Tommy walks through the garden, he notices sprinklers on and a lady washing the pavilion with a hose.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">27</td><td class="print">**Hm...the sprinklers look like they are not just watering the lawn, but also part of the walkway...**</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">28</td><td class="print">Hello! You must be the gardener.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">29</td><td class="print">Yes, my name is Lily.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">30</td><td class="print">I am in charge of maintaining the hotel's garden and lawn.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">31</td><td class="print">How can I help you?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">32</td><td class="print">There's a big problem going on at the hotel right now.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">33</td><td class="print">What kind of problem?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">34</td><td class="print">We're facing a water shortage.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">35</td><td class="print">Unless we find a way to start using less water, there won't be enough for our guests to use.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">36</td><td class="print">Okay, how can I help?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">37</td><td class="print">Is there anything you already do to try to save water?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">38</td><td class="print">Yes! When I mow the lawn, I keep the height of the grass to 5cm or 6cm.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">39</td><td class="print">The shade from the taller grass helps the roots retain water.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">40</td><td class="print">I also leave the grass clippings behind after mowing the lawn.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">41</td><td class="print">Wait, what do grass clippings have to do with saving water?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">42</td><td class="print">Actually, the grass clippings decompose which reduces evaporation!</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">43</td><td class="print">Interesting! I never heard of that before.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">44</td><td class="print">But if we have a water shortage, it won't be enough.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">45</td><td class="print">Do you know if any of the garden hoses have any leaks?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">46</td><td class="print">Leaks? Why do you ask?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">47</td><td class="print">I was with the hotel manager earlier and we found leaks in the plumbing system.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">48</td><td class="print">Ahhh. Well, the garden hoses were recently replaced with new ones that have shut-off nozzles.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">49</td><td class="print">The new shut-off nozzles automatically turn off when they are not used and also can also be adjusted to different pressure levels.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">50</td><td class="print">How about this?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">51</td><td class="print">When I was walking through the garden, I noticed that the sprinklers were watering part of the pavement and you were using a hose to clean the pavillion.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">52</td><td class="print">What if you positioned the sprinklers so that it only waters the lawn.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">53</td><td class="print">You could also use a broom instead of a hose to clean the pavillion.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">54</td><td class="print">Good idea! I can also cut down on how often the lawn is watered.</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">55</td><td class="print">Once a week for an hour is enough for a healthy lawn!</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">56</td><td class="print">Alright, now we're talking...</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">57</td><td class="print">I wonder how the manager is doing?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">58</td><td class="print">Hello? Is there anyone there?</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">59</td><td class="print">Helloooooooo!</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">60</td><td class="print">*You notice several faucets left on with no one in sight*</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">61</td><td class="print">Who left the faucets on?!</td></tr><tr class="print-category"><td class="print">62</td><td class="print">I better turn off them off before any more water is wasted.</td></tr></table></body></html>